1
00:00:02,300 --> 00:00:04,830
(The following content may not be
suitable for viewers under 19.)

2
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:06,970
(Viewer discretion is advised.)

3
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:11,610
(This program includes virtual
and indirect advertisements.)

4
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:15,280
(Names, businesses, places, and incidents
mentioned herein are fictitious.)

5
00:00:44,810 --> 00:00:46,370
What are you doing here?

6
00:00:46,610 --> 00:00:47,580
I told you

7
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:51,150
not to lay a finger on her.

8
00:00:51,450 --> 00:00:53,150
Seriously!

9
00:00:55,150 --> 00:00:57,250
You saw, didn't you?

10
00:00:57,320 --> 00:01:00,690
She came here at night, begging
to be touched, and made me lose it!

11
00:01:01,720 --> 00:01:02,890
Why didn't you answer my calls?

12
00:01:04,060 --> 00:01:05,030
Well.

13
00:01:06,960 --> 00:01:08,160
As you can see,

14
00:01:09,230 --> 00:01:10,670
I've been a bit busy.

15
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:19,440
That doesn't mean you should
break into my home

16
00:01:20,340 --> 00:01:21,480
without my consent.

17
00:01:22,580 --> 00:01:23,950
You're educated enough.

18
00:01:28,580 --> 00:01:29,580
Did you say

19
00:01:30,789 --> 00:01:32,450
you wanted a billion won?

20
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:36,520
I'll send it to you tomorrow,
so walk away.

21
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:42,060
No, you can't take that.

22
00:01:43,259 --> 00:01:46,100
I'll give this to you once you pay me.

23
00:01:47,670 --> 00:01:50,270
You're the one who broke your promise.
Hand it over.

24
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:53,310
I can't do that. I have to live too.

25
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,710
This is my last ace in the hole.

26
00:01:58,310 --> 00:02:00,380
I can't just hand it over.

27
00:02:03,150 --> 00:02:04,490
Do you want to die?

28
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:08,220
Are you threatening me?

29
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:11,160
One call to the cops,

30
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:13,330
and your life is over too.

31
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,300
That's right.

32
00:02:17,829 --> 00:02:19,900
Not just your life,

33
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,370
but her life will be over too.

34
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,910
That would be a great sight.

35
00:02:30,579 --> 00:02:32,150
One call to the cops,

36
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,720
and my life is over.

37
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,720
-And her life is ruined too.
-Yes.

38
00:02:45,090 --> 00:02:50,030
(Episode 14: Man on His Knees)

39
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,800
I told you

40
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,440
not to get cheeky.

41
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:35,240
Just live with me.

42
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,350
You still look okay now,
but you'll be hideous

43
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:40,450
as you get older.

44
00:03:40,579 --> 00:03:43,950
Why do you care
if I become hideous or not?

45
00:03:44,150 --> 00:03:45,920
Just get lost!

46
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:28,230
(The fact that you hired that scum)

47
00:04:28,930 --> 00:04:30,430
(to harass my Jeong-hae...)

48
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:34,300
The fact that you chose such a dirty,
despicable method...

49
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:40,640
is really

50
00:04:41,940 --> 00:04:42,940
unforgivable.

51
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:45,050
Sure.

52
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,520
I can't forgive myself either.

53
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:06,670
Don't give me any excuses.

54
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,600
Get the case file together
and send it to Metro.

55
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,710
Give us a few more days.

56
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:15,340
I gave you months already.

57
00:05:15,410 --> 00:05:17,780
Do you think you'll solve the case
if I give you a few days?

58
00:05:19,450 --> 00:05:20,720
Hand it over

59
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:24,120
and prepare to retire quietly.

60
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:33,030
Son,

61
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:35,630
-you like curry, right?
-Yes.

62
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,370
-Should we make curry today?
-Yes!

63
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:41,370
Then we need potatoes, meat, and onions.

64
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:43,540
What else do we need?

65
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,240
You forgot the most important ingredient.
Curry.

66
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:47,680
That's right.

67
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:53,350
If the potato has a green tint

68
00:05:53,409 --> 00:05:55,450
or looks blackish, it doesn't taste good.

69
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:58,390
Look at this. See how smooth the skin is?

70
00:05:58,690 --> 00:06:01,090
This is good for side dishes.

71
00:06:01,260 --> 00:06:02,360
Feel this.

72
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:05,160
-It's rough, right?
-Yes.

73
00:06:05,230 --> 00:06:07,160
This is for boiling.

74
00:06:07,230 --> 00:06:09,060
-It tastes good boiled.
-For boiling.

75
00:06:09,130 --> 00:06:09,330
Okay.

76
00:06:09,330 --> 00:06:10,600
(Rough: for boiling)
Okay.

77
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,170
Isn't it heavy? Want me to carry it?

78
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,370
This is nothing. It's a piece of cake.

79
00:06:24,450 --> 00:06:28,380
Dad. Should we just cross now?

80
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,250
There are no cars.

81
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,490
Ahn Yu-bin. Attention.

82
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:35,760
A signal is a promise.
A man doesn't break his promise

83
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:37,690
just because there are no cars.

84
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,860
Even if no one is looking,

85
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:42,530
you must keep your promise.
That's a real man.

86
00:06:42,930 --> 00:06:43,930
Understood?

87
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,970
Okay. Sorry. I wasn't thinking.

88
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:51,610
See? It changed because we waited.

89
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:54,710
-Let's go.
-You're the best.

90
00:06:55,940 --> 00:06:58,110
One, two. Good.

91
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:00,850
One, two, three, go. One, two...

92
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:06,250
For potatoes and carrots,

93
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:09,790
cut them into 1cm cubes.

94
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:13,860
That provides the best texture
when you chew.

95
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:15,360
Okay.

96
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,970
I don't like carrots though.

97
00:07:18,130 --> 00:07:20,030
Dad. Can't we take out the carrots?

98
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:21,100
Yu-bin.

99
00:07:21,570 --> 00:07:24,370
If it were for just you and me,
naturally, we'd take out the carrots.

100
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:27,140
But Mom likes carrots.

101
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,880
That's right.

102
00:07:31,550 --> 00:07:33,050
-Dad.
-Yes?

103
00:07:33,610 --> 00:07:35,220
Don't worry about Mom.

104
00:07:37,150 --> 00:07:38,590
What do you mean?

105
00:07:38,650 --> 00:07:41,060
I'll learn how to cook

106
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:42,920
and cook for her.

107
00:07:45,230 --> 00:07:48,159
That's why you're teaching me how to cook.

108
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:53,200
Yu-bin, that's not the reason.

109
00:08:00,010 --> 00:08:01,580
(Mr. Kang of the 1,000th store)

110
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:08,020
Yu-bin, then I'll make

111
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:10,420
carrot juice for you today.

112
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:11,650
No way.

113
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:15,790
(Curry recipe:
Cut potatoes and carrots in 1cm cubes)

114
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:18,930
Dancing is all about confidence.

115
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:23,900
Don't get nervous and stretch out
your chests and shoulders.

116
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,700
Great.

117
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,610
As soon as you stepped into
our dance studio,

118
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:33,809
you already became the best dancer.

119
00:08:36,679 --> 00:08:37,980
I won't make a speech.

120
00:08:38,510 --> 00:08:40,580
You can watch us dance first

121
00:08:40,650 --> 00:08:45,050
and try to awaken the instincts
which lie deep inside of your hearts.

122
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:48,260
Louis 60, please come out.

123
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:02,700
-Right here.
-Thank you.

124
00:10:02,760 --> 00:10:04,130
Here's your dish.

125
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,100
-Thank you.
-Enjoy.

126
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,610
Here you go. Bon appetit.

127
00:10:19,710 --> 00:10:21,050
-Thank you.
-Sure.

128
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,280
You can take this too.

129
00:10:24,220 --> 00:10:26,620
-There it is.
-Here's your dish.

130
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:30,160
You must be a new waitress.

131
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,190
You're just my type.

132
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:34,560
-Hey, young lady.
-Yes?

133
00:10:34,860 --> 00:10:36,300
What's your name?

134
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,900
Enjoy.

135
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:40,870
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

136
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,240
My goodness!

137
00:10:46,610 --> 00:10:48,280
Hon... Honey.

138
00:10:49,810 --> 00:10:50,980
Chun-bok.

139
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:00,820
You call that an excuse?

140
00:11:00,890 --> 00:11:02,890
I said to just focus on raising Pu-reum.

141
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:06,230
How can you work there
no matter how much you love money?

142
00:11:06,290 --> 00:11:08,200
What's so bad about that place?

143
00:11:08,530 --> 00:11:11,200
I just promised to cook in the kitchen.

144
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:13,230
That bar is right in front of our home,

145
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:16,670
and how can you want to work
at Hae-suk's place of all places?

146
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:22,040
Are you embarrassed because of Hae-suk?

147
00:11:22,140 --> 00:11:23,140
What?

148
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:24,750
That's the reason.

149
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,880
I thought you got mad
because you were worried about me.

150
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:31,050
You're mad because you were
humiliated in front of your first love.

151
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:35,020
Yes, I was humiliated in front of Hae-suk.
Are you satisfied?

152
00:11:38,830 --> 00:11:40,700
What are you so humiliated about?

153
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:43,160
It's not like I did something bad.

154
00:11:43,230 --> 00:11:47,070
I was helping out during her peak hours
to make some pocket money.

155
00:11:47,130 --> 00:11:48,270
"Make some pocket money"?

156
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:51,310
If you love money that much,
why did you marry me

157
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:53,470
instead of a rich guy? Why?

158
00:11:54,140 --> 00:11:56,140
Why did you marry a guy like me?

159
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:59,180
Man! Darn it!

160
00:12:25,210 --> 00:12:27,010
Is that the expensive bag?

161
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:29,480
Yes. Honey, look at it.

162
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:34,150
Look at the quality, the color,
and the design. Isn't it amazing?

163
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:37,050
I get to use expensive skincare products
like this thanks to her.

164
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,320
Goodness.

165
00:13:54,530 --> 00:13:56,560
Hey, Mr. Ahn!

166
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:04,340
Why didn't you come in?
Don't leave like that.

167
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:17,550
I have

168
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:20,820
cancer.

169
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:22,690
What?

170
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:28,230
I must be the one being punished

171
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:31,100
for all the bad things I did.

172
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:52,490
Mother.

173
00:14:54,490 --> 00:14:56,920
Hey, Yu-bin. What is it?

174
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:59,030
I made curry with Dad

175
00:14:59,330 --> 00:15:01,360
after school today.

176
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:02,730
Do you want some?

177
00:15:04,330 --> 00:15:07,800
No, I don't have an appetite.
I'll eat it tomorrow.

178
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:11,370
It's good. I put in a lot of carrots too.

179
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:13,740
It's too late. You should go to sleep.

180
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:15,010
Okay.

181
00:15:22,580 --> 00:15:24,150
But Mother...

182
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:33,730
Goodnight.

183
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:51,480
I've been teaching my son to cook.

184
00:15:51,710 --> 00:15:56,050
I was too busy with work
and didn't spend any time with him before.

185
00:15:57,020 --> 00:15:58,590
You're doing very well.

186
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:01,420
It's way more profitable

187
00:16:01,490 --> 00:16:04,790
to spend time with your child
than to go out and make money.

188
00:16:04,890 --> 00:16:07,660
Such times turn into
priceless memories later on.

189
00:16:08,530 --> 00:16:10,430
-Thank you.
-Yes.

190
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,470
I think you're right.

191
00:16:14,270 --> 00:16:17,870
Why didn't I help him make
those priceless memories before?

192
00:16:21,810 --> 00:16:24,350
Goodness, Mr. Ahn.

193
00:16:24,780 --> 00:16:26,810
Are you sure you're all right?

194
00:16:27,050 --> 00:16:29,720
Of course. I'm fine, Mr. Kang.

195
00:16:34,220 --> 00:16:35,590
I used to think

196
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:39,930
it's always better to pretend like
you're tough and strong.

197
00:16:40,390 --> 00:16:42,130
But that isn't the case.

198
00:16:42,930 --> 00:16:45,670
If you act too tough,
you won't have anyone around you.

199
00:16:46,470 --> 00:16:48,840
They leave you thinking
that you don't need them.

200
00:16:52,140 --> 00:16:53,610
So Mr. Ahn,

201
00:16:54,270 --> 00:16:56,710
when times are tough, just say so.

202
00:16:57,650 --> 00:17:00,410
You can depend on someone
and be comforted too.

203
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:05,720
That's what life is all about.

204
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:11,230
Cheers.

205
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,010
You're still up.

206
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,090
Yu-bin

207
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,690
seems to know everything.

208
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:45,290
Yes, it seemed that way.

209
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:48,830
Why don't we tell him the truth
so he doesn't get nervous?

210
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,100
Sure. Let's do that.

211
00:17:52,070 --> 00:17:54,770
I signed a lease for a place.

212
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,970
I found a nice place.

213
00:17:58,770 --> 00:18:00,310
When do you move in?

214
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:03,040
It's vacant,
so I'm moving in the day after tomorrow.

215
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,850
Let's tell Yu-bin tomorrow night.

216
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:10,050
Okay.

217
00:18:12,620 --> 00:18:14,290
Tell me if you need anything.

218
00:18:14,420 --> 00:18:15,420
Okay.

219
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:21,160
Jeong-hae.

220
00:18:24,330 --> 00:18:27,230
Let's not tell my parents
for the time being.

221
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:31,540
Okay.

222
00:18:51,790 --> 00:18:53,290
I found a place.

223
00:18:53,860 --> 00:18:55,130
I move in two days from now.

224
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:58,800
That's good. Congratulations.

225
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:01,100
You should cook for yourself.

226
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:03,040
Don't eat cup noodles all the time.

227
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:05,270
Do you need anything?

228
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:07,410
Why? Will you buy it for me?

229
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:08,840
What do you need?

230
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:12,680
Jung Jae-hun.

231
00:19:13,810 --> 00:19:15,180
I need you.

232
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:19,990
Forget it.

233
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:24,420
You'll feel empty without me.

234
00:19:26,390 --> 00:19:27,760
Will you be okay?

235
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,870
I'm the most comfortable
when I'm alone. Bye.

236
00:19:43,180 --> 00:19:45,210
(My Love Ae-ra)

237
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:54,350
(The person you have reached...)

238
00:19:57,830 --> 00:19:59,090
Why won't she pick up?

239
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,240
-Mom.
(-The person you have reached...)

240
00:20:09,300 --> 00:20:11,740
I... I'll go by myself today.

241
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:12,970
Come out.

242
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:26,920
Honey. Just let Ji-uk go by himself.

243
00:20:38,670 --> 00:20:40,430
(Moon Hong-ryeol)

244
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:42,600
Hey.

245
00:20:42,770 --> 00:20:44,340
(You're not doing anything today, right?)

246
00:20:44,870 --> 00:20:48,110
What do you mean, I'm not doing anything?
I have so much to do.

247
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:50,240
Jang-hwan told me everything, punk.

248
00:20:50,510 --> 00:20:52,110
The 10-billion-won-movie
went down the drain.

249
00:20:52,780 --> 00:20:55,050
(Shut it and come out.
You need to make money.)

250
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:57,780
Where should I go?
What time do I have to be there?

251
00:21:01,890 --> 00:21:05,260
(My Love Ji-uk)

252
00:21:07,860 --> 00:21:10,600
(17 missed calls: My Love Ji-uk)

253
00:21:21,740 --> 00:21:22,840
Mom.

254
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:24,380
Ji-uk.

255
00:21:25,680 --> 00:21:28,280
A person needs to meet someone
suitable for them in order to be happy.

256
00:21:29,350 --> 00:21:31,390
Ae-ra isn't suitable for you.

257
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:34,390
So stop it here, okay?

258
00:21:35,090 --> 00:21:36,460
Before I get angry.

259
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:40,030
If you keep seeing her regardless,

260
00:21:43,230 --> 00:21:44,630
I will kill her.

261
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:06,620
I really can't do this movie.

262
00:22:07,220 --> 00:22:09,060
I just won't do it.

263
00:22:10,820 --> 00:22:12,390
(Please help me out.)

264
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:15,930
(Director Yoon refuses
to work with Ae-ra.)

265
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,970
You help me out.

266
00:22:18,030 --> 00:22:20,330
I absolutely cannot work with her.

267
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,640
What do you mean?

268
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:23,470
You said she was the best.

269
00:22:24,070 --> 00:22:25,670
