00:45:35,690 --> 00:45:38,630
that he won't come in last in his class

541
00:45:39,300 --> 00:45:40,700
on his next test.

542
00:45:41,200 --> 00:45:44,470
He's faking his illness
because he isn't confident.

543
00:45:46,310 --> 00:45:49,240
We have all done that
when we were his age.

544
00:45:51,110 --> 00:45:53,680
Yu-bin, we were all there together

545
00:45:53,750 --> 00:45:56,350
when you were born.

546
00:45:56,750 --> 00:45:58,950
You were really energetic and healthy

547
00:45:59,020 --> 00:46:01,190
even while you were in the incubator.

548
00:46:01,250 --> 00:46:04,260
Yes, of course.
You hung on like a tough little guy,

549
00:46:04,690 --> 00:46:06,160
so we were very proud of you.

550
00:46:07,660 --> 00:46:08,830
Yu-bin.

551
00:46:10,100 --> 00:46:12,730
They came to show their support
like they did back then.

552
00:46:13,100 --> 00:46:16,340
So, my son, you need to get up soon.

553
00:46:16,600 --> 00:46:19,370
You can do it. You can do it, Yu-bin!

554
00:46:24,110 --> 00:46:25,140
Hello.

555
00:46:25,510 --> 00:46:27,480
I'm from the Traffic Team
of Seobu Police Station.

556
00:46:28,010 --> 00:46:30,320
Mr. Ahn, please come with us.

557
00:46:51,300 --> 00:46:54,340
As you can see, this car was speeding,
and the driver hit him and ran away.

558
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:57,710
We believe the driver
may have taken a sleep inducer,

559
00:46:58,340 --> 00:47:01,850
doesn't have a license,
or was driving drunk.

560
00:47:01,980 --> 00:47:05,050
We'll know for sure
once we catch the driver.

561
00:47:05,180 --> 00:47:06,950
You should go back to the hospital.

562
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:10,160
We'll contact you right away
as soon as we find the car.

563
00:47:24,940 --> 00:47:26,210
(Where do you think you're going?)

564
00:47:27,940 --> 00:47:30,510
(I'll give you what you want. Stay still.)

565
00:47:30,610 --> 00:47:33,210
(-You crazy jerk!
-You wanted this too.)

566
00:47:33,880 --> 00:47:35,210
(Stay still!)

567
00:47:35,380 --> 00:47:36,680
(You crazy jerk!)

568
00:47:37,020 --> 00:47:39,620
Detective Cho, your soup is turning cold.

569
00:47:41,020 --> 00:47:42,120
Tae-uk.

570
00:47:42,520 --> 00:47:46,530
Why are you studying that?
We have to hand that over to Metro anyway.

571
00:47:47,030 --> 00:47:49,060
Just come and eat.

572
00:47:53,670 --> 00:47:55,500
(Stop right there!)

573
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:52,930
What are you doing, you lunatic?
Move aside!

574
00:48:53,360 --> 00:48:54,430
Darn it.

575
00:48:54,530 --> 00:48:56,630
What's wrong with him?

576
00:49:16,550 --> 00:49:17,750
Yu-bin.

577
00:49:19,820 --> 00:49:21,950
May I make a confession?

578
00:49:24,290 --> 00:49:25,920
You know,

579
00:49:28,430 --> 00:49:30,960
when I found out I was pregnant with you,

580
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:34,130
I was really thrilled.

581
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:38,370
But I was also worried.

582
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:41,040
I wasn't sure

583
00:49:44,610 --> 00:49:47,310
if I could be a good mom.

584
00:49:51,720 --> 00:49:53,490
I guess you knew.

585
00:49:55,090 --> 00:49:56,890
Because that's when

586
00:49:58,390 --> 00:50:00,430
you stopped eating.

587
00:50:42,400 --> 00:50:43,570
Goodness.

588
00:50:50,810 --> 00:50:54,080
Baby, will you please save Mommy?

589
00:50:55,180 --> 00:50:56,820
My baby.

590
00:50:57,820 --> 00:51:00,150
Mommy is starving.

591
00:51:01,890 --> 00:51:04,020
You must be starving too.

592
00:51:05,360 --> 00:51:08,390
Goodness, baby.
Please help her out. I ask of you.

593
00:51:08,460 --> 00:51:11,400
Okay? Please help her out. Please?

594
00:51:12,160 --> 00:51:13,770
The day after you heard that,

595
00:51:15,730 --> 00:51:18,600
you came out into the world

596
00:51:20,140 --> 00:51:22,070
to help out your mom.

597
00:51:23,640 --> 00:51:26,080
You came out way before your time.

598
00:51:30,180 --> 00:51:31,680
Come to think of it,

599
00:51:32,920 --> 00:51:34,450
you've always been

600
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:40,190
such a great son from the beginning.

601
00:51:41,460 --> 00:51:42,660
But

602
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:46,100
I don't think

603
00:51:49,230 --> 00:51:52,300
I ever thanked you.

604
00:51:59,140 --> 00:52:00,310
Yu-bin.

605
00:52:02,910 --> 00:52:04,480
Thank you

606
00:52:06,790 --> 00:52:07,990
so much.

607
00:52:18,400 --> 00:52:21,500
I want to thank you too.

608
00:52:22,930 --> 00:52:24,000
You're here.

609
00:52:25,140 --> 00:52:26,300
What happened?

610
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:29,780
They'll find the driver soon.

611
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:33,480
Okay.

612
00:52:35,610 --> 00:52:37,080
That must be why

613
00:52:38,520 --> 00:52:40,290
he eats so well.

614
00:52:40,420 --> 00:52:44,390
He couldn't eat while he was in the womb.

615
00:52:44,460 --> 00:52:45,890
He must have regretted that.

616
00:52:49,330 --> 00:52:50,500
I guess so.

617
00:52:51,530 --> 00:52:54,170
Jeong-hae, you should eat something too.

618
00:52:54,430 --> 00:52:56,170
You haven't eaten anything
since yesterday.

619
00:52:56,570 --> 00:52:58,970
I have no appetite.
You should eat something.

620
00:52:59,400 --> 00:53:01,010
I already ate.

621
00:53:01,410 --> 00:53:03,310
Should I get you some porridge?

622
00:53:11,520 --> 00:53:12,720
Ga-yeon.

623
00:53:13,720 --> 00:53:15,120
Hello.

624
00:53:15,220 --> 00:53:17,420
Hey. I'm glad you came.

625
00:53:17,660 --> 00:53:20,630
How did you get here?
What about your academy?

626
00:53:20,730 --> 00:53:22,830
Have you eaten? Have you had dinner?

627
00:53:22,930 --> 00:53:25,160
I don't want to eat dinner,

628
00:53:25,300 --> 00:53:28,470
and I'm ditching the academy today.

629
00:53:29,230 --> 00:53:30,540
You can't do that.

630
00:53:30,640 --> 00:53:33,070
You should still eat
even if you ditch your academy.

631
00:53:33,270 --> 00:53:35,510
Should I get you something to eat?

632
00:53:37,910 --> 00:53:39,140
Last night,

633
00:53:40,280 --> 00:53:43,320
he opened up to me
about something troubling him.

634
00:53:45,620 --> 00:53:47,090
He talked about his troubles?

635
00:53:48,650 --> 00:53:50,420
Yu-bin did that?

636
00:53:54,790 --> 00:53:56,490
Yu-bin will be all right, won't he?

637
00:53:57,260 --> 00:53:58,930
Of course, he'll be fine.

638
00:53:59,160 --> 00:54:01,330
Gung-cheol can't
suffer any more misfortune.

639
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:03,300
This world isn't that cruel.

640
00:54:04,640 --> 00:54:07,640
People's lives can
crumble down in an instant.

641
00:54:08,270 --> 00:54:11,340
I mean, what did Gung-cheol ever do?

642
00:54:11,410 --> 00:54:13,480
Goodness, fate can be so cruel.

643
00:54:13,550 --> 00:54:14,650
You're right.

644
00:54:15,310 --> 00:54:19,080
Anyway, didn't you say
something big happened with your family?

645
00:54:20,990 --> 00:54:22,550
It's nothing.

646
00:54:22,620 --> 00:54:25,660
It's nothing compared
to what happened to Yu-bin.

647
00:54:25,720 --> 00:54:26,890
Don't mind me.

648
00:54:27,190 --> 00:54:31,800
Right. There's no bigger trouble
than seeing your child get hurt.

649
00:54:32,830 --> 00:54:34,230
Anyway,

650
00:54:34,730 --> 00:54:38,040
shouldn't we tell Jae-hun?

651
00:54:38,140 --> 00:54:41,140
Would Gung-cheol want to see him?

652
00:54:41,210 --> 00:54:43,980
But still, he should know. One second.

653
00:54:46,380 --> 00:54:47,610
(Cyborg)

654
00:54:50,620 --> 00:54:51,820
(Ero Hyeong-u)

655
00:54:56,520 --> 00:54:58,390
-What is it?
-Hey, Jae-hun.

656
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:02,030
Yu-bin got into an accident.

657
00:55:02,390 --> 00:55:04,630
He got into a car accident
and is unconscious.

658
00:55:04,730 --> 00:55:07,100
-So?
-Did you just say, "So"?

659
00:55:07,430 --> 00:55:09,400
How could you be so cold?

660
00:55:09,530 --> 00:55:11,070
I'm busy. Bye.

661
00:55:16,910 --> 00:55:18,740
Why? What did he say?

662
00:55:19,010 --> 00:55:20,210
He hung up saying he's busy.

663
00:55:20,310 --> 00:55:23,180
What? He hung up after he heard that?

664
00:55:23,250 --> 00:55:27,120
Yes. Man, this punk is the worst.
We can't even call him a friend.

665
00:55:27,220 --> 00:55:30,920
I didn't think he was that low.
I can't believe this guy.

666
00:55:30,990 --> 00:55:34,130
That jerk. Darn it.

667
00:55:34,230 --> 00:55:37,930
I'm late. I have to get to work. Bye.

668
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:41,900
I'm taking the day off.
I don't think I can work today.

669
00:55:45,340 --> 00:55:47,670
-Chun-bok, are you okay?
-What?

670
00:55:47,740 --> 00:55:49,410
Have you not told your wife yet?

671
00:55:51,710 --> 00:55:53,210
I have to,

672
00:55:53,910 --> 00:55:56,080
but I can't bring it up.

673
00:55:56,150 --> 00:55:58,480
What if it gets worse?

674
00:55:58,550 --> 00:55:59,850
Tell her before it blows up.

675
00:55:59,920 --> 00:56:01,790
That's why I'm taking dance lessons.

676
00:56:02,920 --> 00:56:04,520
What? Dance lessons?

677
00:56:04,620 --> 00:56:06,120
No. No, be quiet.

678
00:56:06,220 --> 00:56:07,530
Let me go. Dance lessons?

679
00:56:07,630 --> 00:56:09,230
Be quiet.

680
00:56:09,290 --> 00:56:10,730
Why are you taking dance...

681
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:12,160
-Why are...
-Stop it.

682
00:56:47,930 --> 00:56:49,030
Are you going somewhere?

683
00:56:49,500 --> 00:56:50,940
I'm going to stop by at home.

684
00:56:51,800 --> 00:56:54,210
Can you drive? Want me to drive you?

685
00:56:54,440 --> 00:56:55,710
I can drive.

686
00:56:56,570 --> 00:56:57,640
Bye.

687
00:57:00,580 --> 00:57:01,650
Jeong-hae.

688
00:57:09,150 --> 00:57:10,260
Hang in there.

689
00:57:17,460 --> 00:57:18,660
Of course, I will.

690
00:57:20,470 --> 00:57:23,370
I'm using my energy for hating you
to hang in there too.

691
00:57:24,800 --> 00:57:27,570
Good. I'm glad.

692
00:57:29,970 --> 00:57:33,210
Gung-cheol is talking to Yu-bin.

693
00:57:34,510 --> 00:57:37,480
I get what you mean. I won't intrude.

694
00:57:46,620 --> 00:57:48,530
He said it was his fault

695
00:57:48,690 --> 00:57:51,530
that the two of you were getting divorced.

696
00:57:52,200 --> 00:57:55,400
That it was because he was learning
how to cook instead of studying.

697
00:57:56,500 --> 00:57:58,970
He said he needed to make money

698
00:57:59,340 --> 00:58:01,210
because you were unemployed.

699
00:58:01,570 --> 00:58:05,240
Hey, Yu-bin. What are you doing here?

700
00:58:06,340 --> 00:58:09,480
You said you'd get tons of followers
and make lots of money.

701
00:58:09,750 --> 00:58:11,050
So what is this?

702
00:58:27,130 --> 00:58:29,930
(Today, we have the future chef,
Ahn Yu-bin.)

703
00:58:33,100 --> 00:58:34,470
(Hello, everyone.)

704
00:58:34,540 --> 00:58:37,680
(I'm Ahn Yu-bin, 38th generation
of the Sunheung Ahns.)

705
00:58:37,740 --> 00:58:39,940
(Why do I want to become a chef?)

706
00:58:40,150 --> 00:58:42,510
(It is because my dad,
whom I like and respect)

707
00:58:42,580 --> 00:58:44,820
(more than anyone in the world
is a great cook.)

708
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:46,320
(My grandfather said)

709
00:58:46,380 --> 00:58:48,750
(a man doesn't belong in the kitchen,)

710
00:58:48,890 --> 00:58:50,050
(but my dad)

711
00:58:50,190 --> 00:58:52,790
(cooks and even does the dishes.)

712
00:58:52,860 --> 00:58:55,030
(I thought he looked really cool.)

713
00:58:56,830 --> 00:58:59,930
(However, you have the lowest grades
in your class.)

714
00:59:00,270 --> 00:59:01,500
(Yes, that's correct.)

715
00:59:01,600 --> 00:59:04,200
(I am bad at school and at sports,)

716
00:59:04,440 --> 00:59:06,270
(but I'm confident in my eating skills.)

717
00:59:06,340 --> 00:59:09,610
(My dad always said you must eat well
for fortune to come to you.)

718
00:59:09,840 --> 00:59:12,810
(That is why I want to become
a great cook like my dad)

719
00:59:13,010 --> 00:59:15,110
(and share fortune with other people.)

720
00:59:15,180 --> 00:59:18,050
(You want to share fortune, you say.)

721
00:59:18,280 --> 00:59:20,850
(That sounds kind of old-mannish.)

722
00:59:21,190 --> 00:59:22,350
(What do you mean?)

723
01:00:08,230 --> 01:00:11,900
Dad. Should we just cross now?

724
01:00:11,970 --> 01:00:14,710
A signal is a promise.
A man doesn't break his promise

725
01:00:14,770 --> 01:00:16,710
just because there are no cars.

726
01:00:17,380 --> 01:00:18,780
Even if no one is looking,

727
01:00:18,840 --> 01:00:21,450
you must keep your promise.
That's a real man.

728
01:00:21,850 --> 01:00:22,880
Understood?

729
01:00:23,110 --> 01:00:25,920
Okay. Sorry. I wasn't thinking.

730
01:00:28,950 --> 01:00:30,150
Yu-bin.

731
01:00:31,160 --> 01:00:32,260
I was

732
01:00:33,460 --> 01:00:35,460
so wrong.

733
01:00:36,290 --> 01:00:39,560
Promises aren't important at all.

734
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:44,070
I was stupid and taught you

735
01:00:45,270 --> 01:00:46,970
something useless.

736
01:00:48,570 --> 01:00:49,910
I'm sorry, Yu-bin.

737
01:00:51,040 --> 01:00:52,380
If there are no cars,

738
01:00:53,080 --> 01:00:55,850
you can ignore the signal and cross.

739
01:00:59,020 --> 01:01:02,990
Who... Who cares about any of that?

740
01:01:05,960 --> 01:01:09,190
I'm sorry, Yu-bin. I was wrong.

741
01:01:11,030 --> 01:01:12,100
And

742
01:01:13,530 --> 01:01:15,900
Mom and Dad...

743
01:01:18,800 --> 01:01:21,070
getting a divorce

744
01:01:21,970 --> 01:01:25,410
is not because of you, Yu-bin.

745
01:01:29,310 --> 01:01:32,950
It isn't because you get bad grades.

746
01:01:34,850 --> 01:01:37,420
It isn't because you asked me
to teach you how to cook.

747
01:01:38,190 --> 01:01:41,790
Both Mom and Dad

748
01:01:43,460 --> 01:01:47,430
were just too tired.
We were exhausted, that was why.

749
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:50,940
It was definitely not because of you.

750
01:01:52,200 --> 01:01:56,270
We love you so much, Yu-bin.

751
01:01:57,580 --> 01:02:00,410
We think so much about you,

752
01:02:01,480 --> 01:02:02,950
Yu-bin.

753
01:02:08,450 --> 01:02:11,160
So Yu-bin, I'm begging you.

754
01:02:11,220 --> 01:02:13,560
Please, wake up. Please?

755
01:02:14,260 --> 01:02:17,500
I'm begging you. I beg you, my son.

756
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:20,970
Please wake up. My son. Please wake up.

757
01:02:21,270 --> 01:02:23,470
Please wake up, my son.

758
01:02:24,940 --> 01:02:26,740
Please wake up.

759
01:02:28,310 --> 01:02:32,880
Yu-bin. Please wake up, my son.

760
01:02:33,910 --> 01:02:35,280
Please, Yu-bin.

761
01:02:37,220 --> 01:02:41,320
Yu-bin... Please wake up.

762
01:02:41,950 --> 01:02:44,060
Yu-bin. Please wake up.

763
01:02:50,400 --> 01:02:53,460
My Yu-bin told his friend

764
01:02:53,830 --> 01:02:56,730
that his mom and dad were getting divorced

765
01:02:57,770 --> 01:02:59,000
and that he was worried.

766
01:02:59,940 --> 01:03:04,210
He thought we were getting divorced
because of him.

767
01:03:05,110 --> 01:03:09,710
He got hit by a car on his way home
after he told her that.

768
01:03:11,750 --> 01:03:15,420
If I hadn't said that,
Yu-bin wouldn't have been hit by that car.

769
01:03:19,560 --> 01:03:22,230
If I didn't tell Jeong-hae
that I wanted a divorce,

770
01:03:22,290 --> 01:03:24,260
Yu-bin wouldn't have been hit by that car.

771
01:03:24,460 --> 01:03:26,130
No.

772
01:03:26,330 --> 01:03:30,000
If I... If I hadn't told him
to abide by the signal,

773
01:03:30,440 --> 01:03:32,670
Yu-bin wouldn't have been hit by that car.

774
01:03:33,000 --> 01:03:34,840
Yes. That's right.

775
01:03:35,170 --> 01:03:37,780
Yu-bin said let's just cross the street,

776
01:03:37,840 --> 01:03:39,480
but I said to abide by the signal.

777
01:03:39,910 --> 01:03:43,580
That... That it's what a real man does.
A real man...

778
01:03:44,480 --> 01:03:47,750
If I hadn't said that gibberish, Yu-bin...

779
01:03:50,790 --> 01:03:52,320
wouldn't have been hit by that car.

780
01:03:57,360 --> 01:03:59,400
I'm the crazy fool!

781
01:03:59,460 --> 01:04:01,970
I'm the one who deserves to die!

782
01:04:03,940 --> 01:04:05,640
Hey.

783
01:04:07,370 --> 01:04:11,140
Who cares about promises?
Promises aren't important.

784
01:04:12,440 --> 01:04:15,010
Everyone does well
even if they live as they want.

785
01:04:15,680 --> 01:04:17,350
Who cares about promises?

786
01:04:17,920 --> 01:04:19,680
Who cares about being a man?

787
01:04:20,020 --> 01:04:23,820
Who cares about any of that? Who cares?

788
01:04:25,620 --> 01:04:27,160
Calm down.

789
01:04:27,830 --> 01:04:29,690
Jae-hun.

790
01:04:30,390 --> 01:04:32,930
Please save Yu-bin. Please save him.

791
01:04:33,000 --> 01:04:35,700
If you save him,
I'll do anything you want.

792
01:04:35,770 --> 01:04:38,540
I'll do everything you tell me to do.

793
01:04:38,600 --> 01:04:40,400
So please save him.

794
01:04:40,670 --> 01:04:43,240
I'm begging you.

795
01:04:43,310 --> 01:04:44,510
I'm begging you.

796
01:04:44,680 --> 01:04:46,410
Please, Jae-hun. Save my boy Yu-bin.

797
01:04:46,480 --> 01:04:49,180
Please save my boy Yu-bin.

798
01:04:50,180 --> 01:04:52,820
Please save my boy Yu-bin.

799
01:04:53,220 --> 01:04:56,090
What did I do that was so wrong?

800
01:04:56,990 --> 01:05:01,090
What did I do that was so wrong?

801
01:05:05,430 --> 01:05:10,570
Why are they taking it out on Yu-bin?

802
01:05:10,640 --> 01:05:12,300
Why?

803
01:05:16,410 --> 01:05:17,810
Yu-bin...

804
01:05:17,880 --> 01:05:21,580
(All of my convictions
